description:
Monet: Impressions of Light
Smithmark | 1994 | ISBN: 0831757779 | English | 150 pages | PDF | 21.2 MB

These handsomely illustrated volumes offer insight into the lives and works of those few unique individuals whose extraordinary creative genius has affected suceeding generations of artists and altered the way we view the world around us. Considering Impressionsim a national French style, Monet painted such diverse subjects as urban scenes, still lifes, landscapes, seascapes, and nature studies, including his famed gardens at Giverny. The full range of the artist's work is covered in this colorful volume
